<div class="wizard_step">Done!</div>
<div class="wizard_instructions">
Congratulations, you've finished setting up your website.  Now it's time to start using it.
<br/>
<br/>
<b>Things you should know:</b><br/>
<ul>
<li><b>Sign In:</b> You need to sign in to your website in order to manage it.  To do this, you click the 'Log In' link in the upper right corner
of your website.</li>
<li><b>Left Click:</b> To manage features of your website, you'll need to bring up a menu using the left-click button on your mouse
(on Mac, hold down the 'control' button on your keyboard and click the mouse).  You can do this on books, series, blog posts, 
events and other things in order to edit them, or create new ones.</li>
<li><b>Top Bar:</b> The top menu bar will show common options, such as creating blog posts.</li>
<li><b>Help:</b> You can click on any '?' icon for more documentation on that feature.</li>
</ul>
</div>

<%= form_tag(setup_path, :method=>"put", :style=>"display:inline") do %>
  <div class="setup_buttons"><%= button_tag "<< Back", :id=>"back_button", :value=>"back", :type=>"back"%><%= button_tag "Take Me To My Website", :id=>"done", :value=>"done", :type=>"button" %></div>

  <%= hidden_field_tag :setup_step, @setup_step %>
  <%= hidden_field_tag :setup_action, "import" %>
<% end %>
<script>
$(function() {
   $("button#done").click(function() {
       window.location.href = "/";
   });
});
</script>
